Water. Where we get it, how much it costs, and its quality are inescapable questions, the answers to which are crucial for life on earth. And as our climate changes due to the impact of human activity on the planet, it will become increasingly necessary to monitor and predict those changes and how they will affect the availability of water. This is why a new report coordinated by the World Meteorological Organization (WMO) highlights the challenges affecting the production of accurate weather data across the globe, and the advantage it provides for adapting to our changing climate.